Title: RANK
Feature:
RANK() OVER (
  [ PARTITION BY partition_expression ]
  [ ORDER BY order_list ]
)
Description: RANK() is a window function that displays the number of a given row, starting at one and following the ORDER BY sequence of the window function, with identical values receiving the same result. It is similar to the ROW_NUMBER() function except that in that function, identical values will receive a different row number for each result.
Examples: SELECT RANK() OVER (ORDER BY 1) AS rank_value;
